Privacy Policy

At Wasatch View, we are dedicated to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency about how we handle your personal data. This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and how we use, store, and share it.

Information We Collect

Personal Data: Name, email address, phone number, and other identifiable information provided by you.

Financial Data: Bank account information, payment details, and transactional data.

Usage Data: Information about how you interact with our services, including logs, cookies, and device identifiers.

How We Use Your Data We collect and use your data to:

Process payments and verify transactions.

Improve and personalize your experience.

Meet regulatory compliance requirements.

Protect against fraud and unauthorized access.

Data Sharing We may share your data with:

Service Providers: External vendors assisting us in providing services (e.g., payment processing).

Corporate Affiliates: Other businesses owned by or connected to Wasatch View.

Government Authorities: When required to comply with legal obligations.

Data Storage and Security Your data will be securely stored in the United States. We use encryption and other safeguards to protect your information from unauthorized access.

Your Rights You have the right to access, update, or delete your data at any time. Please contact us at [Your Contact Information] for assistance.

Updates to This Policy We may update this policy periodically. Changes will be communicated through our website or other appropriate channels.

Contact Us If you have any questions about this policy, please reach out to us at [Your Contact Information].
